



Dear Sir,
Philadelphia 13 March 1776



I was in Virga (from whence I am but just returned) when your favor of the 26th Decr came here, and now I have but a moment before this Gentleman goes off to thank you for it, and to cover a letter from your brother, with the proceedings and ordinances of our last Convention1Gen. Clinton had left Virginia before I did, and was gone to one, but which we do not know, of the Carolinas2Gen. Lee is now here on his way to
[466]
the Southward where he is to take the direction of our and the Carolina TroopsI shall write you fully in a Post or two,3 in the mean time, beg my compls. to your Lady, Mr & Mrs Custis: I am dear Sir Your most affectionate friend

Richard Henry Lee

